@QiuMM thanks for your reply, if  `resultsFuture.get()` has only one element and the element is `Double.POSITIVE_INFINITY`, we should not assign segment on it,but now our processing logic as follows:
>   if (server.lhs <= bestServers.get(0).lhs) { //eg. `<Double.POSITIVE_INFINITY, node1>`
>       if (server.lhs < bestServers.get(0).lhs) {// `but we can't get here`
>      bestServers.clear();
>     }
>     bestServers.add(server);//`so it will be added in bestServers`
>   }

